    <section>
      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Browse integrated job board, review AI-tailored resume for each position, approve and apply. Everything happens in one platform.</p>
      <p><strong>LazyApply:</strong> Install browser extension, browse LinkedIn or Indeed manually, extension auto-fills applications using your single resume profile. Works across external sites.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> AI tailors resumes automatically. You review each one (30-60 seconds) before applying. No manual browsing required—jobs come to you via matching.</p>
      <p><strong>LazyApply:</strong> You must browse LinkedIn/Indeed manually. Extension auto-fills forms but uses same resume for all. Can apply to hundreds per day if you browse enough.</p>

      <h3>Output Quality</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is tailored to match specific job requirements. Higher interview rates because applications are precisely targeted.</p>
      <p><strong>LazyApply:</strong> Uses one generic resume for all applications. Lower interview rates, especially for competitive roles, because applications aren't customized.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Simple setup—create profile, upload resume, start browsing. No browser extensions or external sites needed.</p>
      <p><strong>LazyApply:</strong> Requires browser extension installation and configuration. Must manually browse external job sites. More setup complexity.</p>

      <h3>Friction Points</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Free tier has credit limits.</p>
      <p><strong>LazyApply:</strong> No free tier. Requires manual browsing of external sites. No resume tailoring or job matching. No integrated tracking.</p>
